## Shidong Market vs Mia C'bon Field Investigation

This week, I participated in a field investigation comparing Shidong Market and Mia C'bon. My group observed the differences between a traditional local market and a premium supermarket, including products, prices, customer behavior, and shopping environments.

Through observations and interviews, I learned that culture and target customers influence how businesses operate. Shidong Market focuses more on fresh local products and everyday shopping, while Mia C'bon offers more imported and premium goods. We also examined consumer behavior by recording what different people purchased and discussing the reasons behind their choices.

This activity helped me understand how culture, income level, and customer needs affect market strategies. It also showed me that businesses must adapt to different groups of consumers rather than using the same approach for everyone.
